			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Consider three points against reliance on CHR ROM on the Super NES: <ul><li>As lidnariq ninja'd me, if there's CHR memory on all carts, the cost has to be paid for each cart. On the other hand, the original plan was for every Super NES to to include a DSP-1, but that was cut. And when Sega tried a console upgrade that &quot;only has to be paid for once&quot;, the 32X went over like 99 lead balloons. </li><li>Wider edge connectors need tighter (more expensive) tolerances. </li><li>Even with CHR ROM, it would still need ~16K of RAM for the mode 7 nametable. And by the time you have that much RAM in the bill of materials, you might as well make it a RAM-based system. </li></ul></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

